We are talking about the Rubygem [Thor](http://whatisthor.com/), of course.

### What We Did
Thor is a [RubyGem](http://rubygems.org/gems/thor) that is used to replace rake, sake, and rubigen. However, that is not how Bundler uses it.

We focused on the Command Line Interface (CLI) aspect of Thor.

Yesterday, we created a new gem by following the now dated [RailsCast](http://railscasts.com/episodes/245-new-gem-with-bundler)

Today, we added Thor to our gem to build a command-line interface by reading [What is Thor](http://whatisthor.com/) and [Building your tools with Thor](http://blog.paracode.com/2012/05/17/building-your-tools-with-thor/)

For example, we would be creating a command to run our gem like `rails new` would create a Rails app or running `bundle install` would install the rubygems you need to run your app.

#### How to Run Your Unpublished Gem
According to Andre Arko, there are 3 ways to run it.

+ `ruby -I lib bin/gem_command_name`

+ `bundle exec bin/gem_command_name`

+ `bundle exec gem_command_name`

